= December 2014: SLD Reckoning

After the local elections, the argument comes home. Joanna Senyszyn and other critics push the logic of responsibility: whoever makes the decisions should answer for the results. Miller has not been overthrown, but the cost of central control is becoming visible.

This is not a Gawkowski rebellion yet. Krzysztof Gawkowski is still secretary general, closer to the party apparatus than to an open insurgency.

- @reckoning_close_ranks: Close ranks around Miller.
- @reckoning_open_review: Open a real review of the campaign.
- @reckoning_public_critique: Let public critics speak.

